WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:02.667
             [♪♪♪]

00:15.782 --> 00:16.781
      Master.

00:16.783 --> 00:17.816
                      Oh...

00:17.818 --> 00:20.486
  It is almost 3:00
   in the morning.

00:20.488 --> 00:22.587
You must get some sleep.

00:22.589 --> 00:25.690
          Well, I have to finish
         these reports, Jeannie.

00:25.692 --> 00:26.992
Oh, very well then.

00:26.994 --> 00:28.894
  I will stay here
and keep you company.

00:28.896 --> 00:30.896
                     [YAWNS]

00:35.136 --> 00:37.636
 Oh, look, master.

00:37.638 --> 00:39.238
There is a new movie
  about Cleopatra

00:39.240 --> 00:40.672
   opening at the
  Rialto tomorrow.

00:40.674 --> 00:42.041
     May we go?

00:42.043 --> 00:43.608
         Oh, I'm sorry, Jeannie.

00:43.610 --> 00:46.245
       I'm getting ready for
   an Apollo Earth Orbit flight,

00:46.247 --> 00:47.879
                 and I'm afraid
               I can't take you.

00:47.881 --> 00:49.181
                   Why don't you
                   go alone, hm?

00:49.183 --> 00:50.349
  Oh, no, master.

00:50.351 --> 00:52.351
    I will wait
until you are free.

00:52.353 --> 00:55.387
  Hm. I love stories
about kings and queens.

00:55.389 --> 00:57.423
They are so exciting.

00:57.425 --> 01:00.092
                 Mm-- Yes, sure.

01:02.663 --> 01:04.530
                     [YAWNS]

01:04.532 --> 01:07.199
I wish you would go
      to bed.

01:07.201 --> 01:08.967
             No, it's all right,
               I'm just gonna--

01:08.969 --> 01:10.202
                I'm just gonna--

01:10.204 --> 01:12.704
    Just gonna rest my eyes here
            for a minute.

01:12.706 --> 01:14.639
       Oh...

01:16.310 --> 01:18.310
             [♪♪♪]

01:26.152 --> 01:27.586
           Aw...

01:35.862 --> 01:37.862
             [♪♪♪]

02:24.445 --> 02:26.445
             [♪♪♪]

02:31.217 --> 02:33.217
             [♪♪♪]

03:00.246 --> 03:01.245
  Hi, Doug. Mike.

03:01.247 --> 03:02.781
                           Roge.
        Hi, how you doing today?

03:02.783 --> 03:03.949
                  There you are.

03:03.951 --> 03:05.717
         Well, it'll never
        get off the ground.

03:05.719 --> 03:07.285
               Hiya, Roge.
         You take your physical?

03:07.287 --> 03:08.687
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
                   How'd you do?

03:08.689 --> 03:09.754
    Great, great.

03:09.756 --> 03:11.356
Say, uh, Dr. Bellows
 wants to see you.

03:11.358 --> 03:12.657
                 Yeah? What for?
     I don't know.

03:12.659 --> 03:14.659
      He just said he wanted you
        to drop by his office.

03:14.661 --> 03:16.495
             Did you take
     your examination yesterday?

03:16.497 --> 03:18.196
          Yeah.
       How'd you make out?

03:18.198 --> 03:19.631
   Oh, all right, I guess.

03:19.633 --> 03:22.167
        Well, all I know is,
      he wants you to drop by.

03:22.169 --> 03:24.169
       I guess I better
     get cleaned up, huh?

03:24.171 --> 03:25.170
               Yeah.

03:25.172 --> 03:27.172
             [♪♪♪]

03:32.946 --> 03:33.945
[KNOCKING]

03:33.947 --> 03:35.313
             Come in.

03:35.315 --> 03:37.082
Good morning,
Dr. Bellows.

03:37.084 --> 03:38.749
            Good morning, major.

03:39.252 --> 03:40.685
                  [EXHALES]

03:40.687 --> 03:44.322
Nothing like isometric exercises
    for keeping up body tone.

03:44.324 --> 03:45.790
    [LAUGHING]
Oh, yes, of course.

03:45.792 --> 03:47.658
Major Healey said
you wanted to see me, sir.

03:47.660 --> 03:50.661
              Oh, yes, uh...
         Sit down, Major Nelson.

03:50.663 --> 03:52.663
              You were scheduled
                   to go on

03:52.665 --> 03:54.499
the Apollo Earth Orbit
  Mission this week.

03:54.501 --> 03:57.802
     Yes, sir. I've been working
      on Project Rainbow, and-

03:57.804 --> 04:00.571
           Did you say--?
   Did you say "were scheduled"?

04:00.573 --> 04:03.174
      I'm afraid you're
   not gonna be able to go.

04:03.176 --> 04:05.076
    But I've been training
       for six months.

04:05.078 --> 04:07.412
       I'm aware of that.

04:07.414 --> 04:09.347
      Perhaps you've been
      overtraining, major.

04:09.349 --> 04:11.416
 Well, is there anything wrong
       with my reflexes--

04:11.418 --> 04:13.218
            Oh, no.
    It's not your reflexes.

04:13.220 --> 04:14.552
        It's your eyes.

04:14.554 --> 04:15.553
            My eyes?

04:15.555 --> 04:17.022
 Your right eye, specifically.

04:17.024 --> 04:19.257
Uh, you're suffering
  from eye strain.

04:19.259 --> 04:21.159
     Have you been doing
  an unusual amount of, uh,

04:21.161 --> 04:22.727
reading or paperwork lately?

04:22.729 --> 04:26.030
Well, uh, just the usual reports
     regarding the mission,

04:26.032 --> 04:28.400
  but I'm sure any eye strain
       is just temporary.

04:28.402 --> 04:31.436
        I'm sure it is,
       major, but, uh...

04:31.438 --> 04:33.871
  Meanwhile, you're grounded.

04:33.873 --> 04:36.241
       Sir, you can't ground me,
              I'm-- I'm--

04:36.243 --> 04:38.042
I'm sorry, major.

04:38.044 --> 04:39.844
    I understand
your disappointment,

04:39.846 --> 04:41.479
but as chief medical officer,

04:41.481 --> 04:43.648
it's my responsibility
to evaluate the fitness

04:43.650 --> 04:45.717
of all personnel.

04:45.719 --> 04:47.785
You failed the eye test.

04:47.787 --> 04:49.987
However, I'm gonna give you
another eye examination

04:49.989 --> 04:51.223
in the morning,

04:51.225 --> 04:53.525
so that we can determine
the best course of treatment.

04:53.527 --> 04:55.227
           I see, well, that's--
             That's very kind.

04:55.229 --> 04:58.029
Afterward, um, why don't
you take a month off

04:58.031 --> 05:00.498
and, uh, go fishing
somewhere, hm?

05:00.500 --> 05:01.499
           Well, thank you, sir.

05:01.501 --> 05:02.500
           I hope you don't mind

05:02.502 --> 05:04.102
              if I appeal this
            to General Peterson.

05:04.104 --> 05:05.403
     Mm, no.

05:05.405 --> 05:08.072
      And I've never felt better
         in my life, general.

05:08.074 --> 05:10.442
  Now, Dr. Bellows will tell you
      that with the exception

05:10.444 --> 05:12.544
       of this slight eye strain
            in my right eye,

05:12.546 --> 05:14.245
          I'm in perfect health.

05:14.247 --> 05:18.182
Yesterday, I passed my physical.
   I checked out 100 percent.

05:18.184 --> 05:20.051
           I don't believe
     there's anybody on the base

05:20.053 --> 05:22.119
         that knows more about
      Project Rainbow than I do.

05:22.121 --> 05:23.988
           And, well, after all,
              we're not gonna

05:23.990 --> 05:26.157
           be reading eye charts
             up there, are we?

05:26.159 --> 05:28.859
         So if you would give me
             the green light,

05:28.861 --> 05:30.761
            I can go ahead
     with my preflight briefing.

05:30.763 --> 05:33.698
  I'm sorry to go over your head
       on this, Dr. Bellows,

05:33.700 --> 05:37.335
        but General Peterson
   understands a little bit more

05:37.337 --> 05:39.036
      about these kind of things
             than you do.

05:39.038 --> 05:40.171
        Isn't that right, sir?

05:40.173 --> 05:42.340
      That's right, Tony.
        You're grounded.

05:42.342 --> 05:44.175
             [♪♪♪]

05:44.177 --> 05:46.578
           It's not fair, Roger.
            It's just not fair.

05:46.580 --> 05:48.946
 They give me so much paperwork,
      I can't see straight.

05:48.948 --> 05:50.748
           And then when I can't
            see straight, they--

05:50.750 --> 05:52.350
They don't let me go up
    on the mission.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.651
  Look, I know it's rough, Tony.

05:53.653 --> 05:55.720
       But if they grounded you,
        it's for your own good.

05:55.722 --> 05:58.023
       It'll give you a chance
    to rest and relax your eyes.

05:58.025 --> 06:00.391
There's absolutely nothing
wrong with my eyes.

06:00.393 --> 06:01.593
You know what I missed?

06:01.595 --> 06:03.795
Two lousy, little letters
on the bottom of the line.

06:03.797 --> 06:06.264
The way they're carrying on,
you'd think I was going blind.

06:06.266 --> 06:07.599
             Will you calm down?

06:07.601 --> 06:09.768
 How can I calm down when
somebody's taking my place?

06:09.770 --> 06:11.770
             [♪♪♪]

06:11.772 --> 06:13.037
     Here.

06:13.039 --> 06:15.407
        Two letters, gee, that--
             That's too bad.

06:15.409 --> 06:18.576
 Wait a minute. Wait a minute!

06:18.578 --> 06:20.912
   Could you get Dr. Bellows
  to give you that test again?

06:20.914 --> 06:22.747
     He's giving me a check
        in the morning,

06:22.749 --> 06:23.882
     but what's the point?

06:23.884 --> 06:25.650
         The point is,
   tomorrow you can pass it.

06:25.652 --> 06:26.685
        How?

06:26.687 --> 06:28.152
                 How? Jeannie!
     Jeannie?

06:28.154 --> 06:29.987
Beverley.
             Huh?

06:29.989 --> 06:31.723
Oh, I'm sorry.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.257
No, forget it.
Just forget it.

06:33.259 --> 06:35.393
Now, listen, the last time
  she tried to help me,

06:35.395 --> 06:36.728
I almost got court-martialed.

06:36.730 --> 06:37.895
                       Yeah--
No, no, forget it.

06:37.897 --> 06:39.864
     The space program
and Jeannie just don't mix.

06:39.866 --> 06:41.566
          Yeah, but if a genie--

06:41.568 --> 06:44.503
What's a genie for if she can't
  help when you're in trouble?

06:44.505 --> 06:46.505
Yeah, well, that's
what I used to think, Roger.

06:46.507 --> 06:47.906
         But it doesn't
       work out that way.

06:47.908 --> 06:50.074
Every time she tries to help me,
      I'm in real trouble.

06:50.076 --> 06:51.543
            I mean <i> real</i> trouble.

06:51.545 --> 06:53.578
Now, don't mention this
to her, and I mean it.

06:53.580 --> 06:55.480
                    Yeah, but--
I mean, promise.

06:55.482 --> 06:56.848
                   All right.

06:56.850 --> 06:59.217
     Well, I still think you're
    not seeing this too clearly.

06:59.219 --> 07:01.019
            Not seeing--
    Not seeing this too clearly.

07:01.021 --> 07:03.154
                [CHUCKLING]
               That's a joke.

07:03.156 --> 07:05.824
                 Well, I'll--
             I'll see you later.

07:05.826 --> 07:07.826
             [♪♪♪]

07:37.490 --> 07:38.790
                      TONY:
                 Hello, Jeannie.

07:38.792 --> 07:41.225
Oh, hello, master.

07:42.930 --> 07:44.228
You're home early.

07:44.230 --> 07:45.396
                Yes, yes.

07:45.398 --> 07:46.598
Is something wrong?

07:46.600 --> 07:47.966
                  No, no, no,
              everything's fine.

07:47.968 --> 07:49.367
        Just, just fine.

07:49.369 --> 07:51.202
            Matter of fact,
      I have a surprise for you.

07:51.204 --> 07:52.971
            I'm gonna take you
          out to dinner tonight,

07:52.973 --> 07:54.472
              and then I thought
               we'd go to that--

07:54.474 --> 07:56.875
 That movie you wanted to go to.
    The thing about Cleopatra.

07:56.877 --> 07:59.678
      Oh, master!
What about your mission?

07:59.680 --> 08:01.846
               Oh, they, uh--
            They cancelled that.

08:01.848 --> 08:04.015
  Oh, why did
they cancel it?

08:04.017 --> 08:05.717
     Mm, technical difficulties,
              you know.

08:05.719 --> 08:07.118
  Is that all?

08:07.120 --> 08:09.087
   Tell me what is wrong
and I will take care of it.

08:09.089 --> 08:10.555
                   Uh, no, no,
                 just forget it.

08:10.557 --> 08:13.257
Oh, but master, I know how much
  this mission means to you.

08:13.259 --> 08:14.893
You've been working
 on it for months.

08:14.895 --> 08:16.928
We will go to the movies
    some other time.

08:16.930 --> 08:18.162
         No, no, really, really.

08:18.164 --> 08:19.764
                 I don't need
              any help, Jeannie.

08:19.766 --> 08:23.001
Uh, we're gonna go to the movies
   tonight and then you can--

08:23.003 --> 08:24.703
             You can think
       about what we're gonna do

08:24.705 --> 08:25.704
        for the next four weeks.

08:25.706 --> 08:27.072
The next four weeks?
                       Mm-hm.

08:27.074 --> 08:30.008
             Yeah, yeah, they've
            given me a vacation.

08:30.010 --> 08:31.576
     Isn't that wonderful?

08:31.578 --> 08:33.578
             [♪♪♪]

08:42.121 --> 08:44.255
Major Healey.

08:44.256 --> 08:47.192
     Jeannie, Jeannie, Jeannie,
    I wish you wouldn't do that.

08:47.194 --> 08:49.294
Oh, I am sorry,
 Major Healey.

08:49.296 --> 08:51.429
   But I came here
because I am worried.

08:51.431 --> 08:53.498
            You're worried?
       You wanna feel a tom-tom?

08:53.500 --> 08:56.001
Something has upset
   Major Nelson.

08:56.003 --> 08:57.335
              Who told you that?

08:57.337 --> 08:58.603
Oh, no one told me,

08:58.605 --> 09:01.072
   but I was not born
yesterday, Major Healey.

09:01.074 --> 09:02.440
                  I'll say.

09:02.442 --> 09:04.976
He is not going on his mission,
and he will not talk about it.

09:04.978 --> 09:07.479
         Well, if he's not gonna
         talk about it, I'm not.

09:07.481 --> 09:09.847
   Aw, so there
is something wrong?

09:09.849 --> 09:11.282
              I didn't say that!

09:11.284 --> 09:13.751
Now, look, you be a nice, little
   genie and just run on home,

09:13.753 --> 09:15.853
      and we can talk about this
        some other time, right?

09:15.855 --> 09:17.155
But--
        Now, any time you want--

09:17.157 --> 09:19.124
Major Healey, why are they
   giving Major Nelson

09:19.126 --> 09:21.192
four-weeks vacation?
               Well, why not?

09:21.194 --> 09:23.495
  Please, tell me.

09:23.497 --> 09:25.196
                  I'm sorry,
             my lips are sealed.

09:25.198 --> 09:27.332
   Major Healey...

09:27.334 --> 09:28.866
                  Forget it!

09:28.868 --> 09:30.868
              I promised Tony
           I wouldn't tell you--

09:30.870 --> 09:32.970
            He has bad eyes!

09:34.908 --> 09:36.741
         [GROANING]

09:36.743 --> 09:40.177
        Oh, boy, you certainly
       know how to scare a guy.

09:40.179 --> 09:42.613
Major Nelson has beautiful eyes.

09:42.615 --> 09:44.282
       Yeah, well to you, maybe,

09:44.284 --> 09:47.218
      but he failed his eye test
       and he's being grounded.

09:47.220 --> 09:49.854
No wonder he was so unhappy.

09:49.856 --> 09:51.923
Well, why did he not tell me?

09:51.925 --> 09:55.059
          Maybe it's because
     you didn't set him on fire.

09:55.061 --> 09:58.129
   He did not
wish to worry me.

09:58.131 --> 09:59.663
                 I don't think
              that's the reason.

09:59.665 --> 10:01.733
        Jeannie, if I were you,
      I'd just stay out of this.

10:01.735 --> 10:03.868
   Oh, well, of course
I will not stay out of it,

10:03.870 --> 10:05.937
but he is my master.

10:05.939 --> 10:07.338
I love helping him.

10:07.340 --> 10:09.140
            Well, I don't think
          he loves being helped.

10:09.142 --> 10:10.708
              And, Jeannie,
         will you do me a favor?

10:10.710 --> 10:11.709
          What?

10:11.711 --> 10:13.044
      Don't tell him I told you.

10:13.046 --> 10:15.079
             I'm getting too old
            to make new friends.

10:15.081 --> 10:17.115
   Certainly, well,
 I will say nothing.

10:17.117 --> 10:18.850
                      Well, uh--
Thank you, Major Healey.

10:18.852 --> 10:20.084
               Drop in any time.

10:20.086 --> 10:21.352
      Bye-bye.

10:22.789 --> 10:24.889
         Bring your own matches.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.795
             [♪♪♪]

10:52.619 --> 10:54.018
[CLEARS THROAT]

10:54.020 --> 10:55.754
              Oh, hi, Jeannie.

10:55.756 --> 10:57.155
                 How are--?
            Where have you been?

10:57.157 --> 11:00.191
     Oh, I just went out
to get a breath of fresh air.

11:00.193 --> 11:01.359
                        Oh?

11:01.361 --> 11:03.061
               I worry about you
                 when you're--

11:03.063 --> 11:04.062
         When you're not around.

11:04.064 --> 11:05.797
Oh, do you, master?
                       Hm.

11:05.799 --> 11:08.399
            Yeah, well, I know
         it's silly, but I mean,

11:08.401 --> 11:10.201
     what can happen to a genie?

11:10.203 --> 11:12.470
   Nothing, as long
as her master is happy.

11:12.472 --> 11:13.938
Are you happy, master?

11:13.940 --> 11:16.607
   Oh, yes, yes, I'm very happy.
     Oh, I feel just wonderful.

11:16.609 --> 11:18.009
         I-- I'll tell you what.

11:18.011 --> 11:19.310
                Why don't you go
                 and get ready,

11:19.312 --> 11:20.912
              and we'll get
         the early show tonight?

11:20.914 --> 11:22.313
                  I'm due
          at Dr. Bellows' office

11:22.315 --> 11:24.382
        for a little examination
         tomorrow morning, huh?

11:24.384 --> 11:25.416
Oh, do not worry.

11:25.418 --> 11:27.451
I'm sure everything
will be just fine.

11:27.453 --> 11:28.953
                 [CHUCKLING]
               Oh, sure, sure.

11:28.955 --> 11:30.955
             [♪♪♪]

11:49.943 --> 11:51.542
Have a wonderful day, master.

11:51.544 --> 11:53.812
            Thank you, Jeannie.
           I won't be gone long.

11:53.814 --> 11:55.479
              Um, what would you
               like to do today?

11:55.481 --> 11:57.015
            Go to another movie?

11:57.017 --> 11:59.984
Oh, well, no, master.

11:59.986 --> 12:02.887
  Too many movies
are bad for my eyes.

12:02.889 --> 12:05.589
   Oh, well, um, what do you say
           I pick you up,

12:05.591 --> 12:06.691
     we'll go down to the beach.

12:06.693 --> 12:07.692
        How would you like that?

12:07.694 --> 12:08.927
Oh, well, that--

12:08.929 --> 12:12.096
That would be wonderful,
but, uh, what about your work?

12:12.098 --> 12:14.032
            Oh, they'll find
       somebody else to do that.

12:20.207 --> 12:22.506
     He has beautiful eyes.

12:22.508 --> 12:26.144
       He can see better
than anybody else in the world.

12:29.549 --> 12:31.549
             [♪♪♪]

12:36.456 --> 12:37.788
           [TIRES SCREECH]

13:10.790 --> 13:15.559
        "P-L-D-P-B-T-L-D-P-B-L."

13:20.133 --> 13:23.367
       Aw, good morning,
         Major Nelson.

13:23.369 --> 13:24.735
               Oh, good morning,
                  Dr. Bellows.

13:24.737 --> 13:26.003
Roll up your sleeve,
      please.

13:26.005 --> 13:27.138
             Oh, all right, sir.

13:27.140 --> 13:28.539
How are we feeling
  this morning?

13:28.541 --> 13:30.041
             Well, we're feeling
                  just fine.

13:30.043 --> 13:32.876
              Uh, did you know
           my vision cleared up?

13:32.878 --> 13:34.045
    Has it?
                      Yeah.

13:34.047 --> 13:35.279
Why, that's remarkable.

13:35.281 --> 13:37.381
          Yeah, the eye strain
       just went away like that.

13:37.383 --> 13:38.882
    Did it?
                      Mm.

13:38.884 --> 13:41.085
 Yeah, I, uh, got a good night's
        sleep last night.

13:41.087 --> 13:43.354
It's amazing what a good night's
     sleep will do for you.

13:43.356 --> 13:45.389
        You know, I-I was really
           worried for a while

13:45.391 --> 13:47.391
         I wasn't gonna be able
        to make Project Rainbow.

13:47.393 --> 13:49.226
   And, uh, now,
you're not worrying?

13:49.228 --> 13:50.894
                  [CHUCKLING]
                  No. No, sir.

13:50.896 --> 13:52.296
         I'm not worried at all.

13:52.298 --> 13:54.765
             I think you'll find
            I have 20-20 vision.

13:54.767 --> 13:56.800
    Hm, good.

13:56.802 --> 13:58.135
Blood pressure normal.

13:58.137 --> 14:00.271
           I think you'll find
         everything normal, sir.

14:00.273 --> 14:01.472
         Nothing to worry about.

14:01.474 --> 14:03.240
Mm. All right, major.

14:03.242 --> 14:05.909
 Shall we, uh, read
the eye chart again?

14:05.911 --> 14:07.211
           Yes, sir.

14:07.213 --> 14:09.213
             [♪♪♪]

14:14.653 --> 14:15.819
    BELLOWS:
Sit down, major.

14:15.821 --> 14:17.154
TONY:
Yes.

14:17.156 --> 14:21.492
   Would you like me to start
   at the top or the bottom?

14:21.494 --> 14:23.494
             Why don't you start
                at the bottom.

14:24.464 --> 14:26.197
    We'll try a different chart.

14:32.405 --> 14:34.572
Oh, uh, excuse me
a minute, major.

14:34.574 --> 14:35.840
Uh, I'll be right back.

14:37.977 --> 14:39.710
                Oh, Miss Gordon.

14:39.712 --> 14:42.479
Will you get Major Nelson's file
  and bring it in here, please?

14:42.481 --> 14:44.148
Of course, Dr. Bellows.
     Where is it?

14:44.150 --> 14:47.418
           [STAMMERING]
          "Q-P-O--" No.

14:47.420 --> 14:49.253
"O-P-Q-- O-P."

14:49.255 --> 14:50.255
What is it?

14:50.257 --> 14:52.756
           "O-P... O-P--"

14:52.758 --> 14:54.659
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

14:54.661 --> 14:56.060
Fine, I'll get it
   right away.

14:56.062 --> 14:57.295
                      Thank you.

14:58.598 --> 15:01.198
All right, major.
 Shall we start?

15:01.200 --> 15:03.200
             [♪♪♪]

15:09.842 --> 15:12.409
             TONY:
      Uh, don't you think
  you should wear a robe, sir?

15:12.411 --> 15:13.610
        A robe? What for?

15:13.612 --> 15:15.846
    Well, aren't you afraid

15:15.848 --> 15:17.181
       you'll catch cold?

15:17.951 --> 15:19.450
             [GIGGLING]

15:19.452 --> 15:21.886
      Why would I be afraid
        of catching cold?

15:21.888 --> 15:23.388
           Oh-- Ahem.

15:23.390 --> 15:25.890
         I don't know.
   There's no reason, really.

15:29.395 --> 15:30.395
        Oh, come in.

15:34.734 --> 15:36.567
       BELLOWS:
Thank you, Miss Gordon.

15:36.569 --> 15:38.903
       Will there
be anything else, doctor?

15:38.905 --> 15:41.038
          No, that will be fine.

15:41.040 --> 15:44.041
    Doctor, if you'd like me
         to wait, I'd--

15:44.043 --> 15:45.976
               Of course
       I don't want you to wait.

15:45.978 --> 15:47.978
             You're gonna read
           that eye chart again.

15:47.980 --> 15:49.414
             Yeah?

15:49.416 --> 15:50.981
Nice seeing you again,
        major.

15:50.983 --> 15:54.919
    Oh, well, it's certainly
     been nice seeing you.

16:03.396 --> 16:06.163
Now, major, shall we go on?

16:06.165 --> 16:07.598
          Sir, should she, uh--?

16:07.600 --> 16:09.467
          Should she walk around
                like that?

16:09.469 --> 16:10.834
Walk around like what?

16:10.836 --> 16:12.737
       Well, you saw her.

16:12.739 --> 16:16.274
   She was wearing, you know,
        her underthings.

16:16.276 --> 16:17.508
  Well, I should hope so.

16:17.510 --> 16:18.809
            Hope so?

16:18.811 --> 16:22.847
Major Nelson, can we get on
   with the examination?

16:22.849 --> 16:24.915
       Yes, oh, yes, yes.

16:24.917 --> 16:27.285
 Would you read the bottom line
     of the chart, please?

16:27.287 --> 16:28.952
           Uh, "P-R-I-

16:28.954 --> 16:31.622
           V-A-T-E."

16:31.624 --> 16:33.624
             [♪♪♪]

16:34.961 --> 16:38.162
     Major, I'm afraid
    your eyes are worse.

16:38.164 --> 16:40.498
       You didn't get
   a single letter right.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.167
       Are you joking, sir?
    I can see it right there.

16:43.169 --> 16:45.703
 But it doesn't say "P-R-I-V--"

16:45.705 --> 16:47.037
   That spells "private."

16:47.039 --> 16:48.306
                       Yes, sir.

16:48.308 --> 16:51.242
       It's on a door to a room,
            and there's a--

16:51.244 --> 16:53.411
            There's a conference
           going on in the room.

16:53.413 --> 16:54.712
     I can see through the wall.

16:54.714 --> 16:58.949
  Did you say you could
  see through the wall?

16:58.951 --> 17:01.118
        Yeah-- Did I say
 I could see through the wall?

17:01.120 --> 17:02.620
  BELLOWS:
I heard you.

17:02.622 --> 17:05.922
      You said you could see
 through the walls into the room

17:05.924 --> 17:07.691
            and that there
      was a conference going on.

17:07.693 --> 17:09.193
       Is that
what you said, major?

17:09.194 --> 17:10.595
                     Yes.

17:10.597 --> 17:13.097
    Yes, maybe that's why you're
         in your underwear.

17:13.098 --> 17:15.366
  My underwear?

17:15.367 --> 17:16.666
                      Yes.

17:16.669 --> 17:18.536
    You can see
through my uniform?

17:18.538 --> 17:21.172
                    Yes, sir.

17:21.174 --> 17:26.042
What color shorts
  am I wearing?

17:26.045 --> 17:27.911
                      Blue.

17:27.913 --> 17:29.880
             With your monogram.

17:29.882 --> 17:32.916
    Remarkable.
You have x-ray eyes.

17:32.918 --> 17:34.918
Well, who's in that conference?

17:34.920 --> 17:37.621
            General Peterson,
             uh, Mr. Harris,

17:37.623 --> 17:40.258
               Mr. Rogers
         and Colonel Sackheim.

17:40.260 --> 17:42.726
 Don't go away, major.

17:42.728 --> 17:44.728
             [♪♪♪]

17:50.836 --> 17:52.102
              Jea--

17:52.104 --> 17:54.639
Jeannie! Jeannie.

17:56.142 --> 17:57.241
        How is it going, master?

17:57.243 --> 17:59.109
   Oh, I'll tell you
    how it's going.

17:59.111 --> 18:01.111
You should ask. It's gone.
   I'm-- I'm finished.

18:01.113 --> 18:02.312
       Washed up.

18:02.314 --> 18:04.214
    Oh, but I was only
trying to help you, master.

18:04.216 --> 18:05.650
         Yeah, I-- Don't say it.

18:05.652 --> 18:06.918
       Just please don't say it.

18:06.920 --> 18:08.385
                Who told you
           about my eyes anyway?

18:08.387 --> 18:10.755
I promised Major Healey
that I would not tell.

18:10.757 --> 18:11.989
               I'll kill him.

18:11.991 --> 18:13.624
               I swear, I'll--
               I'll kill him.

18:13.626 --> 18:15.526
      Well, I thought
that if you had x-ray eyes,

18:15.528 --> 18:17.294
they would let you
go on your mission.

18:17.296 --> 18:18.729
                  Mission?

18:18.731 --> 18:20.397
             They won't let me
           outside of this room.

18:20.399 --> 18:22.400
             [♪♪♪]

18:24.904 --> 18:26.704
          The problem could be--

18:28.274 --> 18:29.840
 General Peterson, Mr. Harris,

18:29.842 --> 18:32.209
Mr. Rogers and Colonel Sackheim.

18:32.211 --> 18:33.411
          Dr. Bellows.

18:33.413 --> 18:34.912
He was right.

18:34.914 --> 18:37.381
  Do you realize we're in the
middle of a private conference?

18:37.383 --> 18:39.383
    Uh, yes, sir.
That's why I came in.

18:39.385 --> 18:41.752
 Uh, Major Nelson saw it
from the examination room.

18:41.754 --> 18:45.322
Dr. Bellows, I said we're in the
middle of a private conference.

18:45.324 --> 18:48.225
Uh, uh, general, may I see you
    for a moment, please?

18:48.227 --> 18:50.861
       Oh, uh,
excuse us, gentlemen.

18:50.863 --> 18:53.096
  Major Nelson...

18:53.098 --> 18:56.500
  has x-ray eyes.

18:56.502 --> 18:58.702
        He has x-ray eyes.

18:58.704 --> 18:59.904
Yes, sir.

18:59.906 --> 19:03.774
  Uh, he saw you
through the walls.

19:03.776 --> 19:07.110
  Gentlemen, if you'll excuse me
    for a moment, there's, uh,

19:07.112 --> 19:08.913
                something I have
                to take care of.

19:08.915 --> 19:12.950
     General, this time
you're in for a big surprise.

19:12.952 --> 19:14.518
              All right, doctor.

19:16.689 --> 19:18.522
              Jeannie,
    if you'd stayed out of this,

19:18.524 --> 19:19.590
      I would have had a chance.

19:19.592 --> 19:21.325
            Now, will you please
              stop helping me.

19:21.327 --> 19:23.293
I will do anything you ask.

19:23.295 --> 19:25.963
  All right, then change my eyes
      back the way they were.

19:25.965 --> 19:28.465
I-I am not sure
I can do that.

19:28.467 --> 19:30.968
                What do you mean
                you're not sure?

19:30.970 --> 19:33.203
Well, I have never
done this before.

19:33.205 --> 19:36.941
Uh, must they be <i> exactly</i>
   the way they were?

19:36.943 --> 19:38.542
                    Exactly?

19:38.544 --> 19:40.444
    My-- My mission was scrubbed

19:40.446 --> 19:42.579
     because I missed two little
        letters on that chart.

19:42.581 --> 19:44.915
               Just two!
      Yes, they must be exactly.

19:44.917 --> 19:47.384
I-I will try, master.

19:49.421 --> 19:50.955
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

19:52.025 --> 19:53.124
  JEANNIE:
How is that?

19:53.126 --> 19:55.059
                      Huh?
               What do you mean?

19:55.061 --> 19:58.228
            Oh, uh, Dr. Bellows?

19:58.230 --> 19:59.630
              Dr. Bellows, I-I--

20:00.633 --> 20:01.766
          General Peterson, sir.

20:01.768 --> 20:04.501
         That's the man
      with the x-ray eyes?

20:04.503 --> 20:06.904
Just wait, general.
 It's remarkable.

20:06.906 --> 20:08.773
  Uh, major.
Read the chart.

20:08.775 --> 20:10.908
                  The chart?
             Oh, the chart. Yes.

20:10.910 --> 20:12.076
                      The chart.

20:12.078 --> 20:13.410
   [SMASHING, WATER SPILLING]

20:13.412 --> 20:15.312
        Are you through, doctor?

20:15.314 --> 20:17.715
General, I tell you, this man
 can see through the walls.

20:17.717 --> 20:19.684
Why, he can even see me
   in my underwear.

20:19.686 --> 20:21.952
             My father begged me
             to go into banking,

20:21.954 --> 20:23.253
   and I wouldn't listen to him.

20:23.255 --> 20:24.722
      Major.
                            Yes?

20:24.724 --> 20:26.456
  Tell him, uh--
What am I wearing?

20:26.458 --> 20:28.292
            You're wearing, oh--
             Uh, you're wearing

20:28.294 --> 20:29.293
         your blue uniform, sir.

20:29.295 --> 20:30.394
                   Blue uniform.

20:30.396 --> 20:32.029
  What about
my blue shorts?

20:32.031 --> 20:33.497
        Yes, what about
       your blue shorts?

20:33.499 --> 20:35.800
          Doctor, I'm going back
           to my conference now.

20:35.802 --> 20:37.902
                I don't wanna
             be disturbed again.

20:37.904 --> 20:39.670
             Any questions?

20:39.672 --> 20:41.338
   No, general.

20:41.340 --> 20:43.340
             Oh, I got 'em, sir.

20:43.342 --> 20:46.410
                "M-O-O-R--" Uh--

20:46.412 --> 20:47.477
                     "R-N--"

20:47.479 --> 20:48.579
      Why me?

20:48.581 --> 20:50.047
                    "O-I-T-A."

20:50.049 --> 20:51.415
    I've got it right here, sir.

20:51.417 --> 20:52.649
            Doctor?

20:52.651 --> 20:53.984
  Uh, doctor, don't leave me.

20:53.986 --> 20:56.053
        Doctor, please.

21:01.627 --> 21:04.261
Oh, uh, I'm terribly sorry.

21:06.933 --> 21:09.166
Oh, I'm very sorry, sir.

21:09.168 --> 21:11.401
Please, let me help you.

21:12.905 --> 21:15.472
This section over here, senator,
   is our medical department.

21:15.474 --> 21:16.907
   This is where our astronauts,

21:16.909 --> 21:19.009
        uh, take their preflight
              examinations.

21:19.011 --> 21:21.511
    Uh, these are some of the
 offices of the men around here,

21:21.513 --> 21:23.848
        and as you can see, uh,
       right over the corridor--

21:23.850 --> 21:25.249
                      Excuse me.

21:25.251 --> 21:26.516
                   Uh--
   Who is that?

21:26.518 --> 21:28.085
               That was one
         of our astronauts, sir.

21:28.087 --> 21:30.520
                 And, um--
One of our astronauts?

21:31.124 --> 21:33.224
                 Excuse me, sir.

21:41.166 --> 21:44.568
Oh, coffee machine.

21:50.809 --> 21:53.611
            [SLOWLY]
       "Anthony Nelson."

21:57.916 --> 21:59.950
Tony, what happened to you?

21:59.952 --> 22:01.418
   I'll tell you
what happened to me.

22:01.420 --> 22:03.287
          I got a big mouth
     for a friend, that's what--

22:03.289 --> 22:04.788
             I-I got a big mouth
                for a friend.

22:04.790 --> 22:07.324
                 I asked you
            not to tell Jeannie.

22:07.326 --> 22:08.525
Well, what did she do
       to you?

22:08.527 --> 22:10.260
          What did she do to me?

22:10.262 --> 22:12.362
               She helped me,
            that's what she did.

22:12.364 --> 22:14.030
      How are you feeling,
            master?

22:14.032 --> 22:15.332
                  I'll tell you
                how I'm feeling,

22:15.334 --> 22:16.933
     I'm the only astronaut
         in the program

22:16.935 --> 22:18.335
  that needs a Seeing Eye dog.

22:18.337 --> 22:20.437
            Oh, would you like
          to have a Seeing Eye--

22:20.439 --> 22:21.505
                             No!

22:21.507 --> 22:24.642
         No, I-- I want
     my 20-20 vision back.

22:24.644 --> 22:26.811
Can't you fix him up?

22:26.813 --> 22:29.447
   Well, I must say it is rather
    nice to have him like this.

22:29.449 --> 22:31.315
        This way, he cannot look
             at other girls.

22:31.317 --> 22:32.316
             Yeah...

22:32.318 --> 22:33.551
        Jeannie, please!

22:33.553 --> 22:35.919
      Yes, master, 20-20 vision.

22:35.921 --> 22:37.921
             [♪♪♪]

22:39.758 --> 22:40.891
    Swell.

22:40.893 --> 22:42.960
       What is she do--?
       What is she doing?

22:42.962 --> 22:45.896
            I am working on
      your 20-20 vision, master.

22:45.898 --> 22:48.299
It is not easy.

22:48.301 --> 22:51.668
             Perhaps if you went
              to an eye doctor?

22:51.670 --> 22:53.304
           Oh, please!

22:53.306 --> 22:55.639
           Twenty-twenty vision.

22:58.911 --> 23:00.377
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

23:02.181 --> 23:03.848
         Are you feeling better,
                 master?

23:07.754 --> 23:10.087
         Is that better, master?

23:10.089 --> 23:12.389
Can you see me now, Tony?

23:12.391 --> 23:13.557
                          [THUD]

23:15.528 --> 23:18.061
Oh, master, master.

23:18.063 --> 23:19.563
           Master.

23:21.266 --> 23:22.900
               [YELPS]

23:25.871 --> 23:27.871
             [♪♪♪]

23:29.207 --> 23:32.475
I am so excited that I am going
to play golf with you.

23:32.477 --> 23:33.977
               Yeah, uh, no,
           I'm playing the golf.

23:33.979 --> 23:35.345
             You're gonna caddy,
                  remember?

23:35.347 --> 23:38.248
   Oh, I do not care.
As long as I am with you.

23:38.250 --> 23:41.018
I've been good all week.
Your eyes are fine now.

23:41.020 --> 23:43.153
              Oh, yeah, I got
           my 20-20 vision back.

23:43.155 --> 23:44.588
            Thank you very much.

23:44.590 --> 23:47.157
Oh, I am just sorry that I was
not able to fix them in time

23:47.159 --> 23:48.559
  for you to go up
  on your mission.

23:48.561 --> 23:49.927
           Oh, that's all right,
                  Jeannie.

23:49.929 --> 23:51.227
                   There'll be
                 other missions.

23:51.229 --> 23:53.096
   I had no idea
 that perfect eyes

23:53.098 --> 23:54.731
  were so important
  to an astronaut.

23:54.733 --> 23:57.768
        Oh, yes, perfect vision,
            perfect reflexes,

23:57.770 --> 24:00.136
      perfect hearing, perfect--

24:00.138 --> 24:01.404
  Perfect hearing?
                       Mm-hm.

24:01.406 --> 24:02.906
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

24:02.908 --> 24:05.976
Now you have
perfect hearing, master.

24:07.079 --> 24:09.913
Master, I just gave you
   perfect hearing.

24:09.915 --> 24:11.314
      Master?

24:11.316 --> 24:13.483
   I just gave you
   perfect hearing.

24:13.485 --> 24:15.118
        Master?

24:15.120 --> 24:16.352
       Oh, no. Oh.

24:16.354 --> 24:18.321
        Jeannie, you're kidding.
    Oh, I did it again.

24:18.323 --> 24:19.623
        You've gotta be kidding.
            Oh!

24:19.625 --> 24:20.824
                       Jeannie.

24:20.826 --> 24:22.158
             [♪♪♪]

24:24.262 --> 24:26.262
             [♪♪♪]
